All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BuildOwnController
This controller class allows customers to build their own pizza orders on a JavaFX application This class contains methods to add and remove toppings, as well as various event handlers to handle popups and other events when buttons/checkboxes/combo boxes are selected and/or interacted with.
BuildYourOwn
This class represents a customizable pizza (build your own!) a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
CurrentOrderController
This controller class allows customers to manage and display their current pizza order on a JavaFX application This class contains methods to remove pizzas from an order and calculate total values, as well as various event handlers to handle popups and other events when buttons/checkboxes/combo boxes are selected and/or interacted with.
Deluxe
This class represents a pizza of type "Deluxe" that a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
HelloApplication
This class is the main class for the JavaFX application for our pizzeria and pizza order application! (Runs the application)
MainMenuController
This controller class allows customers to access different windows to place and view pizza orders and is a controller for a JavaFX application's main menu.
Meatzza
This class represents a pizza of type "Meatzza" that a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
Order
This class represents a customer's pizza order and contains methods to get and set information about an order, calculate total costs for the order, and methods to return information about an order in a string representation.
Pepperoni
This class represents a pizza of type "Pepperoni" that a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
Pizza
This abstract class represents the basic layout for the different types of pizzas that a customer can order.
PizzaMaker
This class contains a method responsible for creating instances of various pizza types given a string representation of a pizza.
Sauce
This enum class provides a list of the two types of sauces that can go on the pizzas: tomato and alfredo.
Seafood
This class represents a pizza of type "Seafood" that a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
Size
This enum class provides a list of different sizes for a pizza.
SpecialtyPizzaController
This controller class allows customers to select and order specialty pizzas on a JavaFX application This class contains methods to update displayed pizza price, as well as various event handlers to handle popups and other events when buttons/checkboxes/combo boxes are selected and/or interacted with.
StoreOrderController
This controller class that manages store orders for a JavaFX application.
StoreOrders
This class manages all pizza orders in the store, containing methods to add and remove orders in the store, and get information about various store orders.
Supreme
This class represents a pizza of type "Supreme" that a customer can order, containing methods to return information about a pizza and its price after adding toppings, its size, and extra sauce/cheese.
Topping
This enum class provides a list of different possible toppings for a pizza.
